# SmartCourse — core journey REST collection.
# Works with the VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP Client.
# Run top-to-bottom: register users → create course → publish → enroll → complete.
# Requires the API running: `make api` (with Postgres up) or `make up`.

@base = http://localhost:8000/api/v1

### 1. Register an instructor  -> capture id
# @name instructor
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "prof@example.com", "full_name": "Professor Ada", "role": "instructor" }

### 2. Register a student  -> capture id
# @name student
POST {{base}}/users
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "student@example.com", "full_name": "Sam Learner", "role": "student" }

### 3. Create a course (with a module + assets)  -> capture id
# @name course
POST {{base}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Distributed Systems 101",
  "description": "Foundations of scalable backends",
  "instructor_id": "{{instructor.response.body.id}}",
  "enrollment_limit": 100,
  "modules": [
    {
      "title": "Module 1: Basics",
      "order_index": 0,
      "assets": [
        { "title": "Intro", "type": "text", "content": "Welcome!", "order_index": 0 },
        { "title": "Lecture video", "type": "video", "url": "https://example.com/v1", "order_index": 1 }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

### 4. Publish the course (Phase 1: flips to READY)
POST {{base}}/courses/{{course.response.body.id}}/publish

### 5. Enroll the student  -> capture enrollment id
# @name enrollment
POST {{base}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{ "student_id": "{{student.response.body.id}}", "course_id": "{{course.response.body.id}}" }

### 6. Duplicate enrollment -> expect 409
POST {{base}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{ "student_id": "{{student.response.body.id}}", "course_id": "{{course.response.body.id}}" }

### 7. Update progress to complete (2 assets) -> auto-complete + certificate
POST {{base}}/enrollments/{{enrollment.response.body.id}}/progress
Content-Type: application/json

{ "completed_assets": 2 }

### 8. List the student's enrollments (history)
GET {{base}}/enrollments/student/{{student.response.body.id}}

### 9. Fetch the course
GET {{base}}/courses/{{course.response.body.id}}
